this rich and decadent death by chocolate cake makes for a dramatic show
stopping dessert with chocolate cream cheese icing and ganache sandwiched
between layers of dark chocolate cake it s a chocolate lovers dream
1 cup 250 ml olive oil or another light oil like canola
butter or coconut oil for greasing the pans
1 start by making the ganache preferably the day before if you re using it
2 preheat the oven to 350 f 180 c and grease two 8 inch 20 cm springform baking tins
3 add the eggs to a large mixing bowl and whisk until combined add the milk olive oil and vanilla and whisk again to mix
4 add the flour sugar cocoa baking powder baking soda and salt to the bowl and whisk again to mix there shouldn t be any streaks of flour remaining but be careful not to over mix
5 pour the batter evenly between the two baking tins and bake on the centre rack for 40 45 minutes a toothpick inserted into the centre of the cakes should come out clean when they re done
6 while the cakes are baking make the cream cheese icing follow the recipe instructions but add the 3 tablespoon of cocoa powder to the mix for a chocolate frosting
7 cool the cakes completely before cutting off the domed tops to level them then cut each cake in half lengthwise to create two layers out of each cake
8 layer the cakes in the following order cake cream cheese frosting cake cup ganache cake remaining frosting cake and then coat the top and sides with the remaining ganache
9 chill the cake if not serving immediately and keep leftovers refrigerated wrapped well or in a sealed container
